msgid "Mode:     All Modes"
msgstr "Modo:     Todos os modos"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst
msgid "Hotkey:   :kbd:`RMB` and :kbd:`Shift-RMB`"
msgstr "Atalho:   :kbd:`BDM` e :kbd:`Shift-BDM`"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:15
msgid "The simplest form of object *selection* consists of using :kbd:`RMB` on it."
msgstr "A mais simples forma de *seleção* de objetos consiste na utilização do :kbd:`BDM` sobre o mesmo."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:17
msgid "To *add to the selection*, use :kbd:`Shift-RMB` on more objects."
msgstr "Para *adicionar para a seleção*, use o atalho :kbd:`Shift-BDM` em mais objetos."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:19
msgid "If the *objects are overlapping* in the view, you can use :kbd:`Alt-RMB` to cycle through possible choices (*Object Mode* only)."
msgstr "Caso os os *objetos estejam se sobrepondo* na visualização, você poderá usar o :kbd:`Alt-BDM` para reciclar através das escolhas possíveis (Somente no *Modo de objeto*)."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:22
msgid "If you want *to add to a selection* this way then the shortcut becomes :kbd:`Shift-Alt-RMB`."
msgstr "Caso você queira *adicionar para a seleção* desta maneira, então o atalho se tornará  :kbd:`Shift-Alt-BDM`."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:24
msgid "To *activate an object* that is already selected, click :kbd:`Shift-RMB` on it."
msgstr "Para *ativar um objeto* que já está atualmente selecionado, clique com o :kbd:`Shift-BDM` sobre o mesmo."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:26
msgid "To *deselect* an active object, click :kbd:`Shift-RMB` one time and hence, two clicks if the object is not active. Note that this only works if there are no other objects under the mouse. Otherwise it just adds those to the selection. There appears to be no workaround for this bug."
msgstr "Para *de-selecionar* um objeto ativo, clique com o :kbd:`Shift-BDM` uma vez e novamente, e use dois cliques caso o objeto não seja o objeto ativo. Note que isto somente funcionará caso não haja quaisquer outros objetos sob o ponteiro do mouse. Caso contrário, esta operação simplesmente os adicionará para a seleção."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:35
msgid "Border Select"
msgstr "Seleção por margens"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst
msgid "Mode:     Object Mode and Edit Mode"
msgstr "Modo:     Modo de objeto e Modo de edição"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst
msgid "Menu:     :menuselection:`Select --> Border Select`"
msgstr "Menu:     :menuselection:`Selecionar --> Selecionar por margens`"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst
msgid "Hotkey:   :kbd:`B`"
msgstr "Atalho:   :kbd:`B`"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:45
msgid "To activate the tool use the :kbd:`B`. With *Border Select* you draw a rectangle while holding down :kbd:`LMB`. Any object that lies even partially within this rectangle becomes selected. If any object that was last active appears in the selection it will become active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:50
msgid "For deselecting objects, use :kbd:`MMB` or *Border Select* again with holding :kbd:`Shift` or :kbd:`Alt`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:53
msgid "To cancel the selection use :kbd:`RMB`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:57
msgid "Example"
msgstr "Exemplos"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:61
msgid "Border selecting in three steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:64
msgid "*Border Select* has been activated in the first image and is indicated by showing a dotted cross-hair cursor. In the second image, the *selection region* is being chosen by drawing a rectangle with the :kbd:`LMB`. The rectangle is only covering two cubes. Finally, in the third image, the selection is completed by releasing :kbd:`LMB`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:69
msgid "Notice in the third image, the bright color of left-most selected cube. This means it is the \"active object\", the last selected object prior to using the *Border Select* tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:75
msgid "*Border Select* adds to the previous selection, so in order to select only the contents of the rectangle, deselect all with :kbd:`A` first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:82
msgid "Circle Select"
msgstr "Seleção por círculo"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst
msgid "Menu:     :menuselection:`Select --> Circle Select`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst
msgid "Hotkey:   :kbd:`C`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/tools.rst:92
msgid "*Circle Select* :kbd:`C` is used by moving with dotted circle through objects with :kbd:`LMB`. You can select any object by touching of circle area. It is possible to dynamically change the diameter of circle by scrolling :kbd:`Wheel` or with :kbd:`NumpadPlus` and :kbd:`NumpadMinus` as seen in pictures below. Deselection is under the same principle -- :kbd:`MMB`. To cancel the selection use :kbd:`RMB` or key :kbd:`Esc` or :kbd:`Enter`."
msgstr ""

